post_text:
Restart Committee met last night to discuss new guidelines that came out from the state in regards to close contact and contact tracing. We are seeing more and more schools everyday being partially shut down or multiple students/staff being sent home to quarantine for possible exposure to Covid 19. We are adding additional safety measures as we speak in hopes we can continue to safely educate students face to face. I will have another video update at some point this week to explain the additional guidelines and additional measure we are doing.

Until next time. Have a great day.

Supt. Kuntz

post_text:
District 6 AD's agreed to keep JH VB jamborees on the schedule. We will be touching base weekly to monitor the Covid situation in the area. District 6 AD's also agreed to limit fan attendance to 2 (two) per athlete for jh vb jamborees only at this time. This is to help reduce the amount of possible exposures each school will be faced with when bringing in several towns for an event. We understand the frustrations and inconvenience this may cause, but we feel it is very important to get these kids playing again. Even if that means reduced fan attendance. Thank you and please understand we are attempting to do the best we can under the given situation.

Until next time. Have a great day.

Shawn Kuntz.

post_text:
Good morning Wishek Public School families. There are a few things that I would like to update you on for the coming year:
1. There will be no snack store offered this year.
2. Fresh fruit and vegetable snack will be provided Monday-Friday for grades PreK-8th grade.
3. Graham cracker snacks will still be an option in grades PreK-6th.
4. We are asking that no extra snacks are brought from home.
5. Please leave all extra toys( such as footballs, etc. that would have previously been played with on the playground) at home.
6. Extra school supplies can be brought when needed.

Sorry for the inconvenience that this may cause, but we are trying our best to limit the spread and exposure of COVID-19 to our staff and students. Please realize that this may change, but we will error on the side of caution to begin the year.

Also, all elementary students who are participating in Distance Learning need to come to the school on Friday, August 14 to pick up their computers. 7-12 can pick up their computers on registration day.
Thanks, have a great day.

post_text: Early info in regards to sports physicals for the upcoming 2020-2021 school year. If you had a sports physical last year you will only need to fill out FORM B (included in this post) and submit to your fall coaches if you participate in football or volleyball. For those who don't participate in fall sports, but participate in winter or springs sports fill out FORM B and submit to your Athletic Director. Again, for all returning athletes who had a physical last year you only need to fill our FORM B. This includes elementary age level kids as well. I anticipate this is a one year change per NDHSAA rules to address Covid-19 pandemic. You can also find Form B and regular Physical Form at www.ndhsaa.com

Update: Summer school and summer facility use protocols are being worked on. There are some details/specifics needing to be ironed out yet. As we prepare to return to a normal routine, steps will still be small and restricted. There are still a lot of unknowns as far as the 2020-2021 school year goes. What we do know now is schools have the ability to develop procedures and protocols(under DPI guidance and state regulations) for summer facility use. We will have these protocols established by June 1st and will post update once completed. If anyone has any questions please direct those concerns to Jason Schmidt or myself and not to the coaches. Thank you.

Sincerely,

Supt. Kuntz

post_text:
This is a requirement every even number year.

The Wishek Public School Board invites the public to participate in a school demographic planning meeting to fulfill requirements under NDCC Section 15.1-07-26. This open public meeting will be held on May 11th, 2020 at 8:00 pm at Wishek High School Conference Room. At this forum, the school board will discuss and receive public input on how three- and five-year demographics may impact academic and extracurricular programs, instructional and administrative staffing, facility needs and utilization, district tax levies, and the district’s strategic plan.

Happy May Day, the first day of Military Appreciation Month and our final day of Purple up Week! Today I challenge you to a Military Scavenger Hunt. * A military memorial
* The American flag
* A building utilized by soldiers
* A building utilized by veterans
* Military equipment
* What are the 4 military related holidays we have each year?

Good Luck!

post_text: Extra shout out today for this lovely lady. Ever wonder who has been in charge of preparing the meals that have been provided during this covid-19 period? Sheila Goebel has been a long time assistant cook for Wishek Public School. While many schools are just providing sack lunches, Sheila has been preparing hot lunches for everyone. Despite having her own fears about Covid-19, she understands the importance and value that kids get a hot meal every day. We'd like to extend a special thank you to Sheila for taking charge of the food program during this time.

post_text:
Wishek families and students,
I wanted to take a minute and tell you how proud I am of you all for your dedication to yours and your child/ren’s education! I know this is not the ideal way of learning, but your openness and willingness to continue trying and working together will pay off! All of our student’s at WPS have the potential and ability to be anything they want to be, and at this time they are rocking the distance learning part of their journey. I want you all to remember that we are here for you no matter what. Once again, thank you students and parents for all your extra patience and hard work while we move through this crazy time! I am so honored to be the principal at Wishek a public School!
Mrs. Renae Bosch

PS. Remember to smile and take time growing together as a family during this time as well! My family has had some pretty intense UNO games!

Update from NDHSAA:
NDHSAA Superintendents,

March 13, 2020 2:45 pm

FARGO – On Friday, March 13, due to the Emergency Declaration issued by President Trump the NDHSAA will suspend play at the 2020 NDHSAA Class A Basketball State Tournament and all remaining 2020 NDHSAA Winter Postseason State Tournaments including the 2020 NDHSAA Class B Boys Basketball State Tournament.

In addition to the remaining 2020 NDHSAA Winter Postseason Basketball State Tournaments being suspended, all remaining fine arts and spring sports seasons have been suspended indefinitely, which includes practices and game contests. Further information will be released as it becomes available.

Brenda Schell
NDHSAA Assistant Director

post_text:
Latest update:
To: ND State Educators
From: Kirsten Baesler, State Superintendent
Date: March 13, 2020
Re: COVID-19
NDDPI is working with the Governor’s Office, ND Dept of Health, and the ND Dept of Emergency Services to draft guidance for schools. We are working as quickly as possible while ensuring we provide the most accurate and up-to-date information.

We hope to have something out by the end of the day, March 13. During these times, it is critical that the relationship between all State agencies and local education agencies (schools) be strong and that all communication must be coordinated, consistent, clear, and thorough. We recognize there are many questions.

We appreciate your patience as we work through the necessary state-level coordination.

text: Extra shout out again to one of our students. Interviewing a potential business teacher today who brought along her two children. Obviously moving to a new location can be a tough change for an adult. Making the change as a kid can be even tougher. As we stopped and paused in the hallway for a few minutes this fine young man approached these potential new Wishek students to invite them to teen bowling that was occurring tonight. Talk about helping put a kid and parent at ease!!! Such an awesome display of kindness Mr.Wilson!!
